quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  2,238,"Observe the prayers, and the middle prayer, and stand ye attent before God"
  2,239,"And if ye fear, then afoot or on horseback; but when ye are in safety remember God, how He taught you while yet ye did not know"
  2,240,"Those of you who die and leave wives, should bequeath to their wives maintenance for a year, without expulsion (from their home); but if they go out, there is no crime in you for what they do of themselves, in reason; but God is mighty and wise"
  2,241,"And divorced women should have a maintenance in reason,- a duty this on those that fear"
  2,242,Thus does God explain to you His signs; haply ye may understand
  2,243,"Dost thou not look at those who left their homes by thousands, for fear of death; and God said to them 'Die,' and then He quickened them again? Verily God is Lord of grace to men, but most men give no thanks"
  2,244,"Fight then in God's way, and know that God both hears and knows"
  2,245,"Who is there that will lend to God a good loan? He will redouble it many a double; God closes His hand and holds it out, and unto Him shall ye return"